# honeyfs sample guide
#
# This folder emulates a fake filesystem exposed to attackers.
# Any file you place here appears inside the honeypot path.
#
# Example structure to create:
#   honeyfs/
#   ├── etc/
#   │   └── motd
#   ├── home/
#   │   └── root/
#   │       └── notes.txt
#   └── var/
#       └── log/
#           └── auth.log
#
# Quick example content ideas:
# - etc/motd: "Authorized access only"
# - home/root/notes.txt: fake admin notes
# - var/log/auth.log: fake SSH login attempts
#
# Tip: keep files believable and consistent with your target OS flavor.
